"For my life, I put up many hats in the basketball, even several at the same time when I was president of the BSN, head of the national team and president of the association in the 90s," Reyes recalled when visiting Primera Hora at his home in Bayamón, where he lived with Isabel, his faithful wife for more than 50 years.
"Basketball was my life."
Reyes does not exaggerate with this statement.
The walls of his house are almost all decorated with photos and memories of his long career and testify to them.
